**What**: The missed optimization is the transformation of the expression `add (umax %a, 10), -10` into `usub.sat %a, 10`. This pattern arises when computing the unsigned maximum of a value and a constant, then subtracting that same constant. The result is equivalent to a saturated unsigned subtraction: if `%a < 10`, the result is 0; otherwise, it is `%a - 10`.

