No existing code in `foldAddWithConstant` processes calls to `@llvm.umax`, so this opportunity is missed entirely.

**Impact**: This impacts code quality in domains involving clamping, saturation, or bounds checking (e.g., image processing, audio manipulation). The missed optimization leaves behind unnecessary control flow or multiple instructions where a single `usub.sat` call would suffice. On targets with hardware support for saturated arithmetic (e.g., ARM, RISC-V with Zba/Zbb), this can result in significant performance improvements or reduced code size.

